abstract: Green Bay scored the first 16 points of the game and tied the score after Seattle took a late lead, but the Seahawks quickly drove for a touchdown in overtime, on a 35-yard pass to Jermaine Kearse.
snippet: Green Bay scored the first 16 points of the game and tied the score after Seattle took a late lead, but the Seahawks quickly drove for a touchdown in overtime, on a 35-yard pass to Jermaine Kearse.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — The Seahawks huddled on their sideline Sunday afternoon, and inside the circle, their coach, Pete Carroll, pointed and shouted and waved. Above the din, in a stadium that two hours earlier had been stunned into silence, many players nodded along as he spoke.

abstract: A dispatch from the place where the nation’s most well-regarded grammarians, etymologists and language enthusiasts gather to talk shop.
snippet: A dispatch from the place where the nation’s most well-regarded grammarians, etymologists and language enthusiasts gather to talk shop.
lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Ore. — “It is a solemn and important duty we have,” Allan Metcalf, a grandfatherly looking man, said into a microphone. He was standing in front of a crowd of the nation’s top linguists, many of whom were still flooding into the already packed room. The space was tight, Mr. Metcalf apologized, but the linguists had only an hour. They had to get started.

abstract: “Birdman” and “Grand Budapest Hotel’’ each received nine nominations for the 87th Academy Awards, which will take place Feb. 22. “Boyhood” also was confirmed as a best picture favorite.
snippet: “Birdman” and “Grand Budapest Hotel’’ each received nine nominations for the 87th Academy Awards, which will take place Feb. 22. “Boyhood” also was confirmed as a best picture favorite.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES— Alejandro G. Iñárritu’s “Birdman” and Richard Linklater’s “Boyhood” were showered with honors on Thursday as the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences confirmed what’s been whispered for months: Those are the films to beat at the 87th Oscar show on Feb. 22.

abstract: Senator Cory Gardner’s successful campaign in Colorado provides a template for the Republican future.
snippet: Senator Cory Gardner’s successful campaign in Colorado provides a template for the Republican future.
lead_paragraph: With the demographic composition of the electorate rapidly changing, what is the best way for Republicans in diverse states to campaign? The election in November of Senator Cory Gardner of Colorado provides a template for the party on how to succeed in a battleground state with two ascendant constituencies: well-educated social liberals and increasingly assertive Hispanic voters.
